Class PreviewDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • java.awt.Window
          • java.awt.Dialog
            • javax.swing.JDialog
              • com.dlsc.flexgantt.swing.print.PreviewDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDatelineModelListener, ImageObserver, MenuContainer, PropertyChangeListener, Serializable, EventListener, Accessible, RootPaneContainer, WindowConstants

    public class PreviewDialog
extends JDialog
implements IDatelineModelListener, PropertyChangeListener
    A dialog that can be used to preview the print out of the Gantt chart. The dialog is capable of displaying several pages at the same time and also supports an auto-fit feature that ensures that all pages are always visible (automatic zoom). This feature can be turned off so that the user can manually zoom in and out.
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.7 $
    Author:
    Dirk Lemmermann
    See Also:
